<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFACFFBFC6F45484FD32F9C0" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFACFFBFC6F45484FD32F9C0" blockId="24.[151,1437,1462,1633]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFACFFBFC6F45484FEB6FA71" bold="true" box="[199,315,1463,1489]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFACFFBFC4A05484FCA1FA70" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[659,812,1463,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanesis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFACFFBFC4A05484FCA1FA70" box="[659,812,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">P. yunnanesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFACFFBFC5075484FC02FA71" bold="true" box="[820,911,1463,1489]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FFACFFBFC5075484FC02FA71" box="[820,911,1463,1489]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but different from the latter by longer second section of costa and the shape of sternite VI. In the key to Russian Far East (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFACFFBFC5CA54E9FAEBFA55" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[1017,1382,1498,1525]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref22089" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V. (2000) New species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from the Far East of Russia. Fragmenta Faunistica, 43 (4), 35 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2000.43.4.035" type="journal article" year="2000">Disney &amp; Michailovskaya 2000</bibRefCitation>
), the species runs to couplet 4 on page 44, to female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFACFFBFC4FD54CCFBB6F9B9" authority="Michailovskaya, 1995" authorityName="Disney et Michailovskaya" authorityYear="1995" box="[718,1083,1534,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pullum">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFACFFBFC4FD54CCFCB5F9B8" box="[718,824,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">P. pullum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFACFFBFC50C54CDFBB6F9B9" author="Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[831,1083,1534,1561]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref22359" refString="Michailovskaya, M. V. (1995) A review of the Eastern Palaearctic species of the genus Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae). Far Eastern Entomologist, Vladivostok, 18, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1995">Michailovskaya, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs from the latter by the apical seta shorter than the maximum width of palpus, palisade extending 2/3 of mid tibia and abdominal sternite VI bifurcate with 3 long setae on each lower branch.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
